.TH "LIGHTNING-PEER-DISCONNECT-ALL" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-peer-disconnect-all \- disconnect all currently connected peers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning peer-disconnect-all
.SH DESCRIPTION
Iterates all connected peers from
.B listpeers
and calls
.B lightning-cli disconnect
for each one.
Returns a list of per-peer results.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"disconnected":[{peer_id, ok},...]}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-disconnect (1),
.BR lightning-peer-list (1)
